Currently the only way to suppress emoticon rendering is to edit the wikiFiltersSubsystemContext.xml file. Would be nice if emoticons could instead be enabled or disabled via the administrative interface. If emoticons are disabled they should also disappear from the rich text editor and the notation help.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-4883].
  {panel}

I had to disable the emoticon renderer in the wikiFiltersSubsystemContext.xml file as some of the emoticons were interfering with text strings we frequently use. But this only concerns the "face" emoticons and none of the other emoticons which all consist of a single character surrounded by brackets, e.g. "(?)". It would be nice if it were possible to enable or disable these two sets of emoticons separately.

